                    "description": "PRosPERoS (PRInting PERsonalised orthopaedic implantS):\nDeveloping the smart implant of the future\n\nThe development of new, patient specific orthopedic implants is an extremely complex puzzle. It requires a broad multidisciplinary knowledge and understanding of metallurgy, 3D print technology, computer modelling, mechanics an dynamics, orthopedics, biology, regenerative medicine, animal models and clinical trials.\n\nThe Prosperos project aims to develop personalized, smart, biodegradable and 3D printable implants based on magnesium (Mg) and zinc (Zn) alloys. By accurately scanning the vertebrae with advanced imaging techniques, implants can be designed and printed patient-specifically. This offers enormous potential benefits to the patient in terms of reduced complications and faster recovery times.\n\nThe partners in the projects are (in alphabetical order): Admatec Europe Antleron Brainport Eindhoven Cerapedics Inc. Fited KU Leuven MUMC+ Maastricht University Medanex Clinic, Now Part of NAMSA, Replasia, Smart BioMaterials Consortium (SBMC) Delft University of Technology Eindhoven University of Technology UMC Utrecht and UZ Leuven\nChris Arts\nFor more information go to https://lnkd.in/dpdZN7fN",
                    "title": "Principle investigator Interreg Vlaanderen-Nederland Prosperos-II project",
                    "employment_type": "Full-time"
                }
